{
  "stem": "268.7",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The Elbe-- E-L-B-E-- which was then the demarcation line between the Russian troops and the American troops.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "One day-- and I'll never forget that date because I later on asked the guard, what day is this today?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Again, towards the evening, they blow the whistle.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You come to the assemble place again in the camp, and they say marching orders again.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We did get a-- a ration of bread, next day's bread ration, which I pocketed quickly behind my-- I hid behind my shirt.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I ate half on the-- on the road because I figured I might march all through the night.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I'll save something for later.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we're marching-- and-- and as we're coming close to the Elbe River, I see German troops, Wehrmacht, guarding the entrance of it and rushing us, [? too. ?] And the SS guards kept telling us, schnell, schnell, schnell.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This time we didn't-- we-- we-- all of a sudden, we're-- we're picking up the pace.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We're not anymore marching.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We're jogging and running, already, you know?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And with wooden shoes, it's hard to run.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- and, you know, so you slip and you, you know, fall.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And you can't run.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he kept saying, schnell, schnell.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I didn't realize until after we went through, and I kind of looked back.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I saw a-- a bunch of green uniformed Germans crawling under the bridge and throwing wires and unwinding and rolling wires.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was something going on there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And as they-- as they rushed us along after we passed cross the Elbe River, we were not perhaps maybe a half a mile away, I heard a horrible explosion.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the ground shook on us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I looked back, and there was smoke billowed from-- from the river.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
